            <title><![CDATA[The World Ends with You director Tatsuya Kando leaves Square Enix after 29 years]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/the-world-ends-with-you-director-tatsuya-kando-leaves-square-enix-after-29-years</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/the-world-ends-with-you-director-tatsuya-kando-leaves-square-enix-after-29-years.1203933/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/the-world-ends-with-you-director-tatsuya-kando-leaves-square-enix-after-29-years<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
        </ul>

    
    <p><span>'I will continue doing my best going forward.'</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Tatsuya Kando has left <a title="Companies > Square Enix [5,353 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/square-enix">Square Enix</a> after 29 years, he announced on <a href="https://twitter.com/tatsuyakando/status/1929095512298344457" target="_blank">Twitter</a>. <span id="more-968696"></span></p><p>Kando most notably served as the director of <em>The World Ends with You</em>, <em>The World Ends with You: Solo Remix</em>, <em><a title="Series > Final Fantasy [139 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/series/final-fantasy">Final Fantasy</a>: All The Bravest</em>, and <em>The World Ends with You: Final Remix</em>, as well as series director of <em><a title="Games > NEO: The World Ends with You [16 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/neo-the-world-ends-with-you">NEO: The World Ends with You</a></em>. Outside of directorial roles, he was an animation supervisor on numerous <em><a title="Series > Kingdom Hearts [9 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/series/kingdom-hearts">Kingdom Hearts</a></em> games, as well as various <em>Final Fantasy</em> games.</p><p>“This is a personal matter, but as of May 31, I have left Square Enix,” Kando said in a message. “Over the past 29 years, I’ve had the opportunity to work on many projects, including <em>Final Fantasy</em>, <em>Kingdom Hearts</em>, and <em>The World Ends with You</em>, and the experiences I’ve gained are irreplaceable.</p><p>“The support from everyone who played the games has been incredibly encouraging, and it served as a driving force that pushed me forward in development every day. I’m deeply grateful. Thank you so much!</p><p>“Going forward, I will continue doing my best to create enjoyable content that brings smiles to everyone’s faces.”</p></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
